Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Fixed & Synced by bozxphd\N{\b1\c&H909090&}^.^.^.^.COLORED by.^.^.^.^{\c\b}\N{\b1\c&H404080&}®{\c\b} {\b1\c&H0000FF&}Sud_Arun collections{\c\b} {\b1\c&H404080&}®{\c}\N{\i1}A member of{\i} {\c&H00FFFF&}Psagmeno.com{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.22,0:01:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT CHATTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.03,0:01:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- You like it?\N- All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.44,0:01:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to go. My dad's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.90,0:01:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll see you tonight.\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.66,0:01:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAR ENGINE STARTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.41,0:01:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the dress. Do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.42,0:01:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to hurry. Everyone's going.\NThere's only two left in my size.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.96,0:01:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Dad, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.55,0:01:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CHILDREN PLAYING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.85,0:01:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When do I meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.56,0:01:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,His name's Chappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.94,0:01:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On the football team and very...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.02,0:01:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Chubby?\N- Chappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.77,0:01:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll meet when he picks me up\Nfor the dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.15,0:01:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not before?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.19,0:01:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, you really need to go faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.70,0:02:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he drive you to the dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.70,0:02:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He's rented a limo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.12,0:02:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So he won't drive you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.95,0:02:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Limos come with drivers. So stop worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice dress. You'll be very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.09,0:02:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.62,0:02:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm getting out.\N- No, no, no. Wait until I park.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.41,0:02:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's already inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Fan, careful crossing the street!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAR ENGINE STARTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.33,0:03:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.18,0:03:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}HIGH-PITCHED RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.07,0:04:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MUFFLED ALARMS BLARING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.97,0:04:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT CHATTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PHONES RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.52,0:04:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PHONE RINGS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.69,0:04:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Metro desk, Ian Wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.32,0:04:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MAN THROUGH PHONE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.03,0:04:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,An action wing of the Authentic IRA
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.78,0:04:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,has just exploded a bomb\Nat the OBT Bank in Knightsbridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.82,0:04:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The code word is "Phoenix."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.08,0:04:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Britain's banks are now targets\Nfor the Authentic IRA.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.99,0:04:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The bombings will continue as long as\NBritain's financial criminal institutions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.29,0:04:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,persist in their support of the illegal\Noccupation of Northern Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.13,0:05:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A bomb just went off,\Nan OBT Bank in Knightsbridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.72,0:05:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A group called the Authentic IRA just\Nphoned it in. They're claiming credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's the Authentic IRA?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.97,0:05:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No idea. Never heard of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.35,0:05:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ. There goes the Peace Accord\Nright back in the shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.02,0:05:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up. A bank has just\Nbeen bombed in Knightsbridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A group calling itself\Nthe Authentic IRA just phoned it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.86,0:05:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know who they are,\Nwho's behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.95,0:05:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the Met, Sinn Fein,\Nmonitor the blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.95,0:05:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the IRA or is it something else?\NISIS? Al-Qaeda?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.79,0:05:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you waiting for? Get over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.58,0:05:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIRENS WAILING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.96,0:05:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.26,0:05:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}REPORTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} ...have asked\Na number of police officials
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.47,0:05:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for current estimates\Non the dead and wounded...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.43,0:05:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.77,0:05:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.40,0:06:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}WOMAN SOBBING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.94,0:06:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}FEMALE ANCHOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} This is a major incident\Nthat they're treating
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.49,0:06:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as a possible terrorist attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- The bomb went off at exactly...\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KNOCKING ON DOOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.99,0:06:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,...4:15 GMT in Knightsbridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One theory on the cause of the blast
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.33,0:06:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was that it may have been\Na gasoline explosion underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How many? How many I get?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.92,0:07:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve dead so far,\Nthree times as many injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.63,0:07:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The explosion was centered\Nat the OBT Bank Branch in Knightsbridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.01,0:07:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no warning and police\Nwere taken completely by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.80,0:07:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck warnings. That'll teach 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.93,0:07:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Any problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- No.\N- We should be moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's normal procedure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Every cop, hotel, and landlady in London\Nis now looking for the Irishman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This place is safe,\Nso long as we stay put.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.91,0:07:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE VIBRATING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.51,0:07:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I go to jail\Nif I murdered your phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.56,0:08:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Destruction of government property?\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.48,0:08:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CHUCKLES SOFTLY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\NToo bad. What's the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.48,0:08:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost 10:00. Ten more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.53,0:08:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I'll miss my flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.57,0:08:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's stay here,\Ndoor locked, blinds down...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.62,0:08:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Room service for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound good?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And your work, Deputy Minister?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.08,0:08:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,An acute case of food poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.17,0:08:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MAGGIE CHUCKLES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to work on your excuses, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.39,0:08:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE VIBRATES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.35,0:08:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.53,0:08:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been an IRA bombing in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.37,0:09:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Scores dead and injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.04,0:09:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE VIBRATING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes?\N- Jesus, Liam.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.26,0:09:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Half the world's trying to find you.\NDo you even know what's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.68,0:09:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes, I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MARY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I've been trying you for hours.\NWhere've you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.22,0:09:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.22,0:09:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- Meetings?\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.31,0:09:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOG BARKING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.48,0:09:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.77,0:09:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't come home. I was worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.69,0:09:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Came in late, left early.\NLot of work to catch up on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.11,0:09:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But the guest room wasn't slept in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.03,0:09:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Who said I slept?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.66,0:09:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, cut the crap, Liam.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.33,0:09:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't come home, plain and simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.04,0:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if I didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.16,0:09:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I've got a lot to deal with, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.33,0:09:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, don't wait up, and don't be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.25,0:09:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunday is the 20th anniversary\Nof my brother's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.30,0:10:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Saint Mary's is dedicating\Na mass to him, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.14,0:10:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have Beth put it in the calendar, OK?\NWe'll talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.89,0:10:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.94,0:10:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT CHATTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.65,0:11:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand\Nthe need for swift action.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.32,0:11:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But until we can identify the threat,\Nthere's not much we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you have your finger\Non the pulse over there, Liam.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.37,0:11:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're depending on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you can provide, anything at all,\Nwould be a tremendous help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.25,0:11:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm meeting the Council now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.83,0:11:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll shake the trees as hard\Nas I can and see what falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.75,0:12:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Kate, this is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.88,0:12:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We've managed to keep the lid on this\Nfor 19 years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.76,0:12:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are new upstarts in the ranks\Npressing for the way things were.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.85,0:12:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I could use something now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.89,0:12:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know what I'm referring to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.02,0:12:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Royal Pardons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.98,0:12:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember your list, the 40 "On-the-Runs."\NAre we really back to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.23,0:12:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My cousin's on that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.53,0:12:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn't even been convicted\Nof any paramilitary offenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are suspects\Nin many things, including murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.41,0:12:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are critical\Nto holding the peace together now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.58,0:12:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A few letters of pardon\Nwould be a small gesture.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.96,0:12:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ELEVATOR BELL CHIMES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- We keep it quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.25,0:12:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But knowing it's been considered,\Ngives me leeway
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.67,0:12:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to press certain men\Nfor something in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.05,0:12:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As Irish Deputy Minister,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.93,0:12:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you have served the British\Ngovernment honorably,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.80,0:12:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which hasn't always been easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But appeasement is a dangerous thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.81,0:12:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} These are longstanding issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.14,0:12:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DAVIES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} That if addressed now\Nwould smack of appeasement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.10,0:12:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I need something, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.77,0:13:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The newer members haven't\Nlived the bloodshed and are easily swayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.15,0:13:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to hold this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.36,0:13:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A gesture is all.\NIt would make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll consider it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.20,0:13:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want something first,\Nsomething real.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.91,0:13:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.89,0:13:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BELL JINGLES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.36,0:13:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.44,0:13:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIZZLING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're closed. We open at 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.66,0:13:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, we're looking for the owner,\Na Mr. Quin Minh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.71,0:13:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Quan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.42,0:14:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LEVETT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} They were found on site,\Nnot far from your daughter's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.38,0:14:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you positively identify them as hers?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.47,0:14:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.76,0:14:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As of now, sir, we don't know,\Nbut we're going to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.14,0:14:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why my daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.73,0:14:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there someone we can call
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.57,0:14:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to come and be with you, Mr. Quan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.91,0:14:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no more family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.29,0:14:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,These bombers, will you catch them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.00,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.34,0:14:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they get punished?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.09,0:14:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BARRIE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Yes, they certainly will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LEVETT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} We'll let ourselves out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.77,0:14:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR CLOSES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.98,0:15:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}VOICES ECHOING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.03,0:15:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, good morning, Hugh. Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.28,0:15:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Been a long time, Liam.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, indeed.\NGo on, take a chair, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.87,0:15:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} All right, Hugh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.41,0:15:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we're all here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.74,0:15:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,does anyone know\Nwho this Authentic IRA is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.83,0:15:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they even part of the IRA?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.79,0:15:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Some new upstarts\Nor something else entirely? Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.47,0:15:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to undermine everything\Nwe've achieved over the last 19 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I won't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.01,0:15:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have the support of the people\Nwho said no to the violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.23,0:15:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Our mandate's to uphold that choice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.27,0:15:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and maintain the Peace Accord\Nno matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.56,0:15:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we in agreement?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.73,0:15:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of support for their actions\Namongst the younger ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.65,0:15:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hotheads.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.32,0:15:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hotheads who don't remember\Nor know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.36,0:15:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You were once one of those hotheads, Liam.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.08,0:15:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago, when it was the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.66,0:16:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did it give us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,More graves than I care to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.25,0:16:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This bombing rivals Omagh\Nwith its civilian deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.42,0:16:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unacceptable, anytime, anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.26,0:16:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you think the bombers\Ncome from our ranks?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.51,0:16:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Brits ID'd the explosive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Czech-made Semtex from our dumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.89,0:16:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ELEVATOR BELL CHIMES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- They also used our code word.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.60,0:16:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means they have\Na contact in our command.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.65,0:16:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.82,0:16:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to divide us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,put the Brits back on the streets again,\Nstir up the troubles all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I won't have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.91,0:16:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a complete check\Nof all the arms dumps here and abroad,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.41,0:16:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,everything verified,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.79,0:16:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,guns, Semtex, the whole fuckin' lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.42,0:16:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PATTY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Jesus, you can't be serious.\N- Never been more so, Patty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.75,0:16:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We check 'em, and if something's missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.96,0:16:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we trace it back\Nto those who knew the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.51,0:16:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we deal with this internally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.30,0:17:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless someone here's got a better idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.93,0:17:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we get in return?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.81,0:17:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.69,0:17:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so bad, Brennan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.98,0:17:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't you paid enough in family blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.24,0:17:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, unless you all\Nwant to trash what we have,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.95,0:17:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your full support and respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.78,0:17:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a complete list\Nof all the stocks within the week,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.74,0:17:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,along with their locations,\Nand everyone who knows where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.87,0:17:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And no fuckin' exceptions!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.17,0:17:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT CHATTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.35,0:17:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.93,0:17:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We backtracked 47 minutes.\NClearly anticipated the CCTV.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.73,0:17:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He circled London for quite some time\Nprior to the bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.35,0:17:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the first\NCC feed we have on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.86,0:17:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Heading southbound on the A413\Nnear Wendover at 10:53 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.94,0:17:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We retrieved the serial number\Nfrom the bike's frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.57,0:18:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was reported stolen\Nin Reading the night before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.37,0:18:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The license plates were also stolen\Nfrom another bike in Reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.62,0:18:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What about phone calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.33,0:18:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming that the bomb\Nwas phone-activated,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.58,0:18:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we've dumped the five closest towers\Nto the blast zone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.00,0:18:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to ID any call terminating
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.67,0:18:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- at the time of the incident.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PHONE RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.79,0:18:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.34,0:18:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.92,0:18:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Bromley.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}OFFICER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} He's here again, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.72,0:18:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- The Chinese man.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.97,0:18:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chinaman.\NIt's five days in a row, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.85,0:18:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ. Tell him I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.93,0:18:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I did, and he said he'd wait, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.11,0:18:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I assure you, this investigation\Nis our top priority, Mr. Quan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.11,0:18:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're doing all we can\Nand pursuing every possible lead
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to find those who killed your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.41,0:18:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're a difficult people to catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.37,0:18:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And it may take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.58,0:18:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.34,0:18:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You must catch these men,\NCommander Bromley.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.00,0:18:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, it's our top priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.72,0:19:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty thousand pound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.35,0:19:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All I have for the names of the bombers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.32,0:19:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry, but we can't take this.\N- Then please tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.32,0:19:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just give me the name\Nof someone in the IRA.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.20,0:19:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To be clear, these are vicious men\Nwho take pride in their atrocities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.33,0:19:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Any attempt by you to contact them\Nis likely to end very badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.46,0:19:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our work, not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.13,0:19:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have you been\Nin this country, Mr. Quan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.89,0:19:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Since 1984. I'm a British citizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.72,0:19:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You were born in Guangxi, China.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.31,0:19:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm Chinese Nung.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.98,0:19:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I work in Saigon after the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We escaped to Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.86,0:20:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we immigrate here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.70,0:20:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You had two daughters\Nbefore Fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.83,0:20:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Both killed during the escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.50,0:20:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- And your wife?\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.37,0:20:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is she now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.25,0:20:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}VOICE BREAKING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\NShe died, giving birth to Fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.80,0:20:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I'm truly sorry for your loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.35,0:20:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But you mustn't keep coming here\Non a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.56,0:20:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't help, and diverts time\Nand resources from our investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.19,0:20:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.94,0:20:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.78,0:20:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for seeing me,\NCommander Bromley.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.63,0:21:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.09,0:21:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MALE ANCHOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} After three weeks\Nof investigations,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.38,0:21:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there's little in the way\Nof solid leads that I'm aware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.26,0:21:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The public is looking for reassurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.89,0:21:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One leading politician\Nwho somberly may have answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,lies uncomfortably\Nat the center of this storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.31,0:21:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We go now to an interview\NI recorded earlier in Belfast
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.98,0:21:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with Deputy Minister Liam Hennessy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.32,0:21:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Deputy Minister Hennessy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.74,0:21:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you've publicly condemned the bombings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.78,0:21:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, as a former leader of Sinn Fein
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.70,0:21:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and a member of the IRA,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.37,0:21:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you took part in similar events years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.99,0:21:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the essential difference between\Nthose acts you were involved in then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.37,0:21:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's happened in London recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.54,0:21:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope. We had none,\Njust years of vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.42,0:21:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KNOCKING ON DOOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.59,0:21:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We needed to break the cycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.63,0:21:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so we committed\Nto a political path which lead to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.84,0:21:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SPEAKS CHINESE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I've made you tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.43,0:21:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ANCHOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} So, if you say "hope,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,why are these IRA men,\Nwho come from your own ranks,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.52,0:21:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,returning to the bombings?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.52,0:22:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I can say with reasonable certainty\Nthat the IRA are not behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.28,0:22:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They stand firmly behind\Nthe agreement and the promises...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.49,0:22:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SPEAKS CHINESE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\NYou can't be like this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.28,0:22:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You should eat something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.91,0:22:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.91,0:22:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting you some noodles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.79,0:22:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ANCHOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} So, you're saying\Npossibly it's a financial problem
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.50,0:22:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than a political one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.75,0:22:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,People look for scapegoats, for a way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.13,0:22:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And for some, they are more than happy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.17,0:22:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to resort to violence,\Nto upset the status quo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.39,0:22:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepared for your signature.\NThey absolutely must be signed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.65,0:22:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CLEARS THROAT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} What's the latest reaction\Non social media?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.28,0:22:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Same as before. Fear and anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.74,0:22:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger directed at whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.15,0:22:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,From the Prime Minister on down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.70,0:22:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,CNN and The Irish Times\Nwant interviews with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.16,0:22:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do tonight\Nor tomorrow morning at 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.16,0:22:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow morning by phone. What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.79,0:23:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You've a call waitin' on Line Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.62,0:23:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Waiting?\N- For 30 minutes now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.96,0:23:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A Mr. Quan from London, very insistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.92,0:23:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- What does he want?\N- His daughter was killed in the bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.22,0:23:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried my best to console him,\Nbut he really just wants to speak to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.39,0:23:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- He saw ya on TV.\N- Oh, Christ, Beth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.47,0:23:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Civic duty. Take it and be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.31,0:23:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR SHUTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.27,0:23:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CLEARS THROAT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.19,0:23:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Liam Hennessy. How may I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.98,0:23:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Mr. Hennessy,\Ntell me who killed my daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.57,0:23:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What on Earth makes you think\NI know who killed your daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.41,0:23:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you are the First Deputy Minister
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.08,0:23:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and advisor to Sinn Fein,\Nand a former IRA member.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.58,0:23:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I am truly sad for your loss, Mr. Quan.\NI have a daughter myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.50,0:23:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I condemn these acts of violence,\Nbut I can't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.84,0:23:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please tell me someone
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.38,0:23:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,who might know the names of the bombers,\Nsomeone I can talk to.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.80,0:23:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any connections\Nto those sorts of people. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.14,0:23:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe you, Mr. Hennessy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.31,0:24:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You are very powerful man.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.39,0:24:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I work for the government\Nand our elected officials.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.81,0:24:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not work for terrorists.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.19,0:24:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,IRA politics and terrorism\Nare different ends of the same snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.11,0:24:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Whichever end you grab,\Nyou still grab a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.61,0:24:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes a great deal\Nof difference which end you grab,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.20,0:24:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because one end will bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.70,0:24:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, I'm sorry for your loss, Mr. Quan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.71,0:24:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.46,0:25:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KNOCK ON DOOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.55,0:25:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR OPENS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.18,0:25:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SPEAKS CHINESE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.30,0:25:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to stop this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.68,0:25:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This wasn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.65,0:25:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SPEAKS CHINESE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I failed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.40,0:25:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.11,0:25:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SPEAKS CHINESE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\NThe restaurant is now yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.62,0:25:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been a good friend to me, Lam.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.29,0:25:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No more of this talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.04,0:25:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.26,0:25:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going home. I'm staying the night.\NI will sleep on the couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.51,0:25:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And on Monday,\NI'm taking you to see someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone to help you.\NBut no more of this talk. OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.69,0:26:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Quan!\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAR ENGINE STARTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.79,0:26:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.01,0:27:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SPEAKS CHINESE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I've been calling you\Nall night. Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.47,0:27:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.05,0:27:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ENGINE STARTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.97,0:27:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When will you come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.63,0:28:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a room?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.09,0:28:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,These are important documents\Nthat we must have today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.01,0:28:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I will keep trying\Nthe sender because,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.93,0:28:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,apparently there's nothing else I can do,\Nwhich I find strange
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.76,0:28:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and certainly not the service\NI've come to expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.35,0:28:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, 329174-N for November.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.69,0:28:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell your supervisor\NI'll be calling back.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.23,0:28:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.73,0:29:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? May I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.61,0:29:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I would like to\Nspeak to Mr. Hennessy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.20,0:29:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- And your name?\N- Ngoc Minh Quan.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.32,0:29:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who's been phoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.99,0:29:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Yes. I phoned many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.62,0:29:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid the Deputy Minister is busy\Nand won't be able to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.58,0:29:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will wait.\N- No, you must leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.75,0:29:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Best do as the lady says.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.00,0:29:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been phoning up\Nat all hours asking for Liam.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.47,0:29:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't take no for an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.42,0:29:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Just groceries.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.68,0:29:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Go now, before we make ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.22,0:29:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- No. I'm wait.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.02,0:29:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the man who's been\Nphoning you from London.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.36,0:29:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a knife on him.\NOne of those Swiss Army types.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.49,0:29:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, take it off him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.87,0:29:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, how much damage\Ncan he do with you two around?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.25,0:29:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.21,0:29:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} As I explained before...\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR CLOSES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.75,0:29:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...I don't know who the bombers are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.92,0:30:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I realize you're angry,\Nbut there's not much I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.00,0:30:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also very dangerous\Nfor you to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.51,0:30:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,People in Belfast\Nwon't take kindly to your accusations.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.80,0:30:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do not know who they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.60,0:30:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like you to please find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.44,0:30:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.19,0:30:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been affiliated\Nwith the IRA for 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.98,0:30:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was,\NI fought hard against the violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.19,0:30:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to prison\Nfor what I did and paid my debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.20,0:30:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I serve the politics of both sides,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.03,0:30:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to heal the wounds\Nand bridge the divide.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.79,0:30:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, my sincere condolences,\Nbut there's nothing I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.96,0:30:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What if your wife and daughter\Nwere killed by bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.59,0:30:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd do everything in my power\Nto get justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.72,0:30:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I've chosen you, Mr. Hennessy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.68,0:30:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You will tell me who killed my child.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.10,0:31:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.07,0:31:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You will change your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.11,0:31:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for seeing me,\NFirst Minister Hennessy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.29,0:31:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.41,0:31:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BLOWS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.48,0:32:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR OPENS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.23,0:32:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Liam. He took me by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.91,0:32:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}FIRE ALARM RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.54,0:32:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're OK, Beth. OK, you're OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.29,0:32:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Take her, take her.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BETH GASPING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.08,0:32:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- Murphy, have the boys check the building.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MURPHY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.04,0:32:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.13,0:32:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.51,0:32:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.97,0:33:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like a whiskey, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.31,0:33:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.57,0:33:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose it would be a waste of time\Nasking who might've done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.03,0:33:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No one comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.11,0:33:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it appears to have been\Nnothing more than a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.16,0:33:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, it wasn't a serious bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.83,0:33:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had been, we wouldn't\Nbe here talking, would we?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.92,0:33:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free to reach out,\Nshould you have the unexpected urge.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.13,0:33:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll feed the press a gas leak story\Nin the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.30,0:33:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fair enough. Thanks very much, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.85,0:33:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PHONE RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.76,0:33:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.56,0:33:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.73,0:33:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You come to my office\Nand plant a fucking bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.78,0:33:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Have you changed your mind?\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Changed my mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.07,0:34:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you out of your fuckin' tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.24,0:34:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no idea who you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.45,0:34:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll soon find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.74,0:34:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.00,0:34:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I'll tell you what.\NLet's meet face-to-face.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.62,0:34:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll settle...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.46,0:34:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The fuckin' wanker\Nthreatened me and hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.13,0:34:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Let's check all the hotels\Nand guest houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.97,0:34:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't be hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.01,0:34:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuckin' Chinaman.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.14,0:34:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.35,0:34:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle Liam? What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.94,0:34:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIREN WAILS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.32,0:34:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.00,0:34:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.50,0:34:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.04,0:34:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.59,0:34:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}EXHALES FORCEFULLY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.00,0:35:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE CHIMES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.79,0:35:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}TIRES SCREECH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAR UNLOCKS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.93,0:35:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Hold it, hold it,\Nhold it! Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.52,0:35:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move! She's wired to blow!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.90,0:35:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}EXHALES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.64,0:36:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}EXHALES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.06,0:36:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Two sets of wires\Nten-foot long,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.44,0:36:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,soldered to that light bulb\Nand covered with ground-up match heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.98,0:36:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Gives an extra kick.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.15,0:36:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not needed, but a nice touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.74,0:36:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Crude, effective, and easy to spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.95,0:36:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he wanted us to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.70,0:36:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Well, it wasn't in the tank,\Nso it wouldn't have worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.29,0:36:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He just wants you to know\Nhe can get to ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.16,0:36:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.62,0:36:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Micky.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.96,0:36:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We found him.\NA B&amp;B in Wellington Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.80,0:37:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} They found him.\N- Grab him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.55,0:37:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Drag him out of Belfast.\NDiscourage him from returning.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.34,0:37:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Wait for me. I'm on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.72,0:37:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE VIBRATING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.64,0:37:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.39,0:37:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DAVIES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I hear your office was bombed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.68,0:37:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LAUGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Hardly.\NIt was the toilet in the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.40,0:37:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,An Asian man in his 60s with a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.06,0:37:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all being taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.52,0:37:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.61,0:37:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} His child died in the bank bombing.\NHe thinks I know who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.28,0:37:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not the only one of that mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.45,0:37:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- So, where are we with the pardons?\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DAVIES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Lots of resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.12,0:37:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if you give us something useful,\Nthings might turn in your favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.75,0:37:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have a lead. I'm pursuing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.92,0:37:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's hope it bears fruit.\NPeople here want heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.46,0:37:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The dogs won't stay leashed much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.80,0:37:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}TIRES SCREECH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.30,0:37:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAR DOOR OPENS AND SHUT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.73,0:37:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Top floor on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.70,0:38:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}FOOTSTEPS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
