Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.16,0:39:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ALL GRUNTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.51,0:39:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SCREAMS, GROANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.39,0:39:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GROANING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.11,0:40:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MCMAHON{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Fuckin' get him!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.69,0:40:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN YELLS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.91,0:40:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.79,0:40:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH PANTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.34,0:40:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Christ Almighty,\Nare you dumb and blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.55,0:40:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,An old man making fools\Nout of the lot of you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.80,0:40:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's still running around\Nout there, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.60,0:40:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You are four men. Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.94,0:40:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We had him cornered,\Nthen he jumped off the roof
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.98,0:40:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and slid down like some fuckin' monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.81,0:40:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MARY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} What is goin' on?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.61,0:40:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM BREATHES HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.57,0:40:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pack your bag. You're going to the farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.49,0:40:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.07,0:40:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Get your things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.32,0:40:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOORBELL RINGS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.66,0:41:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR OPENS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.83,0:41:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CHRISTY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You all right, Sean?\N- Hi, Christy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.91,0:41:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on through, he's expecting ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.63,0:41:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat ya up. Come on in\Nand have a drink, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.71,0:41:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, look at ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.34,0:41:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jesus, the place looks well.\N- It's not bad, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.30,0:41:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} No.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You're a sight for sore eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.35,0:41:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how is New York treatin' ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.93,0:41:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Ah, it's cold.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.68,0:41:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Murphy filled me in, there.\NThat bloody Chinaman.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.06,0:41:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CHUCKLES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} He set off a bomb in my office,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.61,0:41:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,put one in my Jag, and beat the bejesus\Nout of Mick and Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.28,0:41:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Do you want me to handle him?\N- No. That's Kavanagh's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.74,0:41:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help with the London bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.29,0:41:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Any idea who's behind it yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.33,0:41:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.50,0:41:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, the Yanks aren't happy, Liam.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Mm...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.71,0:41:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Dead women and kids\Nall over the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.42,0:41:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Any fundraising now is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.05,0:41:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is not about fundraising, Sean.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.97,0:42:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to go to London\Nand meet someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.31,0:42:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A Richard Bromley in SO15.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.19,0:42:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,SO15?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.31,0:42:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs to know the bombings aren't ours,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.65,0:42:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we're working the problem hard,\Nbut we need his help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.03,0:42:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.94,0:42:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a decorated Ranger\Nin the Royal Irish Regiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.41,0:42:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Bromley will respect you as much\Nas he's capable of respecting any of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.16,0:42:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Should anyone find out\Nthat we're talking to the Brits,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.83,0:42:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to go after one of our own, rogue or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.58,0:42:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,there'll be the devil to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.05,0:42:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, can I count on you, Sean...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.42,0:42:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to be discreet?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.64,0:42:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.22,0:42:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CAR RADIO PLAYING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.40,0:42:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.37,0:43:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}TIRES SCREECH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.93,0:43:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MAÃ®TRE D'{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Right this way, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.35,0:43:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.65,0:43:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You took your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.86,0:43:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I just had to put out\Nthe odd fire here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.87,0:43:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.08,0:43:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.46,0:44:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE CHIMES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.06,0:44:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.02,0:44:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE CHIMES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.46,0:44:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Morrison.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.34,0:44:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander Bromley.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.05,0:44:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} We're not responsible.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.31,0:44:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Forensic evidence and the use\Nof your code word suggests otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.35,0:44:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a renegade unit.\NWe don't know who they are yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.10,0:44:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling me\Nthere's an active IRA unit
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.02,0:44:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,on the loose you know nothing about?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.36,0:44:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.65,0:45:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} And the Semtex?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.44,0:45:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} They're raiding our dumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.78,0:45:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Dumps that were\Nall given up for the Accord?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.45,0:45:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And your code word?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.95,0:45:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're being helped by someone\Nin our command, Belfast or Dublin.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.99,0:45:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you want, Mr. Morrison?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.54,0:45:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We've a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.91,0:45:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Different codes will be given\Nto each member of command.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.46,0:45:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When the bombers claim credit\Nfor the next attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.38,0:45:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll tell us which word they use.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.71,0:45:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll know who gave\Nthe orders and then we end it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.51,0:45:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who else is involved in this plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.34,0:45:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Liam Hennessy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.93,0:45:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can appreciate\Nthe need for discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.26,0:45:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Liam knows\Nwho will be given which word.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.06,0:45:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Hennessy will personally work with us\Nto take out an IRA cell?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.97,0:45:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- A rogue cell.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Your people, nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.77,0:45:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've one condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.19,0:45:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When Hennessy finds the bombers,\Nhe tells me directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.11,0:45:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we take them down. Not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.74,0:45:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is non-negotiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.22,0:46:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We found some plastic bags in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.48,0:46:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on what I saw,\Nhe's brewed up some nitroglycerin,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.06,0:46:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,mixed it with weed killer, packed it\Ninto some plastic plumbing pipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.65,0:46:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How much damage can he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.28,0:46:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm guessing he's made four bombs,\Neach enough to blow up a lorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.78,0:46:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.86,0:46:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Knows what he's doing.\NI've half the city looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.91,0:46:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When he surfaces in Belfast,\Nwe'll find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.33,0:46:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be safe here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.46,0:46:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye. I wouldn't count on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.97,0:48:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.81,0:48:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOG BARKING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.11,0:48:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}TIMER BEEPS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.50,0:48:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Benny!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.84,0:48:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GASPING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.77,0:49:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PANTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.33,0:49:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.50,0:49:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MUFFLED GROANING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.78,0:49:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ALARMS RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.95,0:50:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MEN SHOUTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.96,0:50:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Move it! Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.37,0:50:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MEN CONTINUE SHOUTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.30,0:50:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus. He roughed up Benny and Sean.\NThey'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.14,0:50:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Get more men from Belfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.48,0:50:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've underestimated him.\NIt won't happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.91,0:50:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's another warning, Liam?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.33,0:50:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Aye. Nothing I can't handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.50,0:50:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First Belfast, now here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.75,0:50:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How in God's name\Nare you handling anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.88,0:50:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem's being dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.17,0:50:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MARY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} He is destroying our farmhouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.38,0:50:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,intent on God knows what,\Nand you're calling it a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.09,0:51:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God, you can be so pompous sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.64,0:51:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm leaving for London.\NGonna stay at Keri's.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.27,0:51:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.72,0:51:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I wasn't asking for your permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.23,0:51:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's hardly likely to know\Nabout our daughter's flat, and besides,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.23,0:51:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's you he's after, not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.73,0:51:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the point is,\Nif he knows about the farmhouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.69,0:51:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I assume he knows about Keri's flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.40,0:51:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not worth the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.65,0:51:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, you're just gonna\Nhave to handle it, like you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.03,0:51:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember a time when you would've\Ndealt with this, properly,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.75,0:51:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and other things, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.21,0:51:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But those days are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.09,0:51:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SWITCH CLICKS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.07,0:51:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR OPENS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.45,0:52:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Weighs a bit more,\Nbut shouldn't be noticeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.66,0:52:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All I'm adding is the Semtex,\Na micro-chip and a few inches of wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.66,0:52:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks good.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.62,0:52:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Tricky part will be getting it through\Nthe scanner, but, we'll find a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.75,0:52:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it's turned on?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.71,0:52:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shorter battery life,\Nbut it'll work, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.42,0:52:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Any idea which plane yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.76,0:52:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We don't want to hit a flight\Nwith any Irish on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.60,0:52:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One in the queen's fleet'd be best.\NWe just need the right mule.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.06,0:52:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE VIBRATES AND CHIMES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.35,0:52:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Code word has changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.98,0:52:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As of tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.32,0:52:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}IAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} My news editor's a complete twat.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.49,0:52:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Spends as much on a pair of shoes as I get\Nfor eight hours writing crap like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.24,0:52:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes perfect sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.04,0:52:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who doesn't like a new pair of sexy shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.87,0:52:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You should try a real whiskey.\NTwo Jamesons, single malt.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.50,0:53:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"Wife Attacks\NHusband's Transgender Lover."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.67,0:53:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Some serious news you're writing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.88,0:53:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it pays, I'll write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.05,0:53:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Beats being knee-deep\Nin a bloody bomb site.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.85,0:53:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- So, what do you do?\N- Wealth management.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.86,0:53:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Maggie.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.11,0:53:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ian.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.32,0:53:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT CONVERSATION{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.16,0:53:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} All right.\NI'll call if we need more.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.20,0:53:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thanks, Mary.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} All right, thanks. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.08,0:53:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Six more men\Nare on their way from Belfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.50,0:53:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When they get here, they'll relieve\Nthe fellas who've been up all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.71,0:53:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it enough to secure the farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.88,0:53:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Secure as it can be.\NIt's 20 total working two shifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.72,0:53:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. You're flying\Nto London today with Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.39,0:53:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right, yeah.\N- That's completely unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.05,0:53:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Get her into Keri's flat,\Nthen move them into a hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.72,0:53:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I can manage this, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.23,0:53:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll not be debating this!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.52,0:53:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nick's gonna fill up the Jag.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.44,0:53:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're leaving...\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}EXPLOSION{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.54,0:54:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.50,0:54:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Take him to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.04,0:54:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- Get Mary to the airport. Go.\N- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.30,0:54:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SNIFFS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.89,0:54:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Buried nitro bomb, detonated by remote.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.18,0:54:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He needed a line of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.68,0:54:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Those woods, that's where I'd be.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.64,0:54:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go.\N- Sean! Mick! Get in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.65,0:54:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.30,0:55:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.97,0:55:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PANTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.05,0:55:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys spread out.\NI'll take the high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.65,0:55:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.75,0:55:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.10,0:55:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.77,0:56:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GROANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.57,0:56:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Names!\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GUNSHOT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.69,0:56:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GROANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.74,0:56:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GROANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.21,0:56:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH PANTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.34,0:56:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}EXHALES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.05,0:56:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.01,0:56:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One ol' man running circles\Naround the lot of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.68,0:56:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it so hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.52,0:56:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's ahead of us every step of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.69,0:56:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We need more men.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.06,0:56:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KAVANAGH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} We need 100 more men, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.98,0:56:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we did that,\Nwe'd have the whole of Belfast against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.53,0:56:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring in a tracker,\Nsomeone who knows the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.66,0:56:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and beat him at his own game.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.41,0:57:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My nephew?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.91,0:57:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye. If you can spare him.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.01,0:57:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOORBELL RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.95,0:57:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.16,0:57:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How's Keri? Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.96,0:57:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Out.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.25,0:57:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a wee bit early,\Nbut I'm nearly ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.75,0:57:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you a restaurant in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.05,0:57:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't given it much thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.01,0:57:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what urgencies\Nbring my nephew all the way to London?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.56,0:58:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A few personal matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.02,0:58:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I made the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.56,0:58:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm. I think that works.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.48,0:58:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.32,0:58:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.20,0:58:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MARY MOANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.42,0:58:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.09,0:58:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.88,0:58:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be kiddin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.81,0:58:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Liam?\N- Tell Bromley I'll accept his terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.48,0:58:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pass it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.69,0:58:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I've given out the code words.\NNow we wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.02,0:58:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Quan hit us again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.69,0:58:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Blew up the Jag,\Nput Billy in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.24,0:58:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Kavanagh and the boys went after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.11,0:59:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The wee shitey injured three more men.\NPunji sticks, if you can believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.33,0:59:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Liam, it sounds like he's trained.\NMaybe Special Forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.66,0:59:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Which brings me to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.29,0:59:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I need a tracker, Sean.\NCan you give us a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.75,0:59:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll take a morning flight.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Good man.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.35,0:59:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MARY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Hey. How'd he sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.27,0:59:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.11,0:59:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a lot going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.40,0:59:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if he doesn't\Nfind the bombers, the Accord's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.82,0:59:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And politically, so's he.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.11,0:59:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think he'll find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.78,0:59:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if there's another blast.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.33,0:59:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The code word will lead us to\Nwho's running them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.46,0:59:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's finished.\NThe code word won't save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.29,0:59:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What the Council needs is new blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.25,0:59:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,someone stronger, like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.80,1:00:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He's afraid to use his power.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.88,1:00:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just a washed-up old man\Ntrying to hold onto whatever he can.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.64,1:00:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never forgiven him\Nfor my brother Patrick.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.52,1:00:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Liam found out who killed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.98,1:00:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A UVF death squad. Four men.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.86,1:00:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I told Liam to kill them\Nbefore they got to court.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.66,1:00:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But he said no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.04,1:00:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That the time for revenge is past.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.92,1:00:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, my Patrick is dead and buried,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.04,1:00:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're sitting in jail now,\Nall four of them,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.34,1:00:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,taking classes at the open university.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.80,1:00:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CRYING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} It's not right. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.40,1:00:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}THUNDER RUMBLES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.55,1:01:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}FLESH SIZZLING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.36,1:01:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GUNFIRE{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PEOPLE SHOUTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.15,1:01:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SPEAKS MANDARIN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.90,1:01:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GUNFIRE CONTINUES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.87,1:01:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}WOMEN SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.37,1:01:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT SHOUTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.17,1:02:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.38,1:02:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GIRLS SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.81,1:02:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GROANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.02,1:02:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GIRLS SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CRIES OUT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.34,1:03:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KNOCKING ON DOOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.51,1:03:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hugh McGrath's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.10,1:03:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you're checking my dumps.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.23,1:03:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're checking everyone's. No exceptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.65,1:03:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Four came up short. Two were yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.40,1:03:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten kilos of Semtex missing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.15,1:03:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What in God's name are you doing?\NMy dumps were off-limits.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.78,1:03:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We were clear in that. Remember?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.16,1:03:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You were at the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.95,1:03:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you knew they were short,\Nyou should've handled it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.99,1:03:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They were in perfect order.\NI checked 'em myself, and that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.54,1:04:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ, Liam, so the committee\Nknows it's my Semtex?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.84,1:04:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't know who we can\Ntrust anymore. Do we?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.55,1:04:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust, or fear?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.22,1:04:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In your case, mostly fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.81,1:04:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple and brutal, like my da taught me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.77,1:04:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, we have an opportunity here, Liam,\Nif you take the lead.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.90,1:04:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This Chinaman isn't helping matters,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.40,1:04:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but let me get some locals\Nto hunt him down.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.98,1:04:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- How much do you know?\N- Plenty.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.99,1:04:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Bomb in your office. Your farm. Your car.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.53,1:04:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary and your daughter hiding out\Nin a London hotel, a bloody mess, it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.58,1:04:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the men sense weakness, as do the UVF.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.00,1:04:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be back in Belfast,\Nout in front, taking charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.96,1:04:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look, I'm no politician...\N- What're you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.59,1:04:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The bombing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.26,1:04:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A few quiet words of encouragement\Nwould soothe the ranks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.05,1:04:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Encouragement"?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.47,1:04:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They kill civilians by the buckets.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.10,1:05:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They went a bit far, I know,\Nbut they have given us real momentum.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.39,1:05:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Brits are on the ropes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.85,1:05:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ, I said hit a few\Nfinancial targets. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.98,1:05:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No one gets hurt.\NThat's what we agreed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.65,1:05:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- You gave me your word.\N- And by God, I kept it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.78,1:05:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who they are,\Ndon't even know who's controlling 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.45,1:05:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the way it has to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.83,1:05:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, if something goes wrong,\Nthey could trace 'em straight back to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.95,1:05:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Go wrong? This wasn't the fuckin' plan.\NI needed this to get our people back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.25,1:05:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- You and I have spent our whole lifetime...\N- You don't give a shit about those men.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.80,1:05:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You needed the bombing\Nto shore up the election,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.09,1:05:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to prop up your weakness in the ranks.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.05,1:05:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, guess what?\NIn the fog o' war, plans fuckin' change.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.18,1:05:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I stood by you\Nwhen you put fire into the lads.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.23,1:05:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,M62, Aldershot, Mountbatten.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.44,1:05:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You were calling for an escalation then,\Nright enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.73,1:05:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Those days are long gone!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.03,1:05:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I heard a few months ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.66,1:06:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the old Liam,\Na man back on track with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.00,1:06:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't forgotten\Nwhat we're fighting for, have ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.37,1:06:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You question my loyalty?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.63,1:06:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I buried my brother-in-law,\Nbefore that my da and my two cousins.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.92,1:06:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We spilt our fair share of blood\Nstruggling for united Ireland,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.38,1:06:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,not profiting off a divided one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.51,1:06:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, don't fucking go asking me again\Nif I've forgotten what we're fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.68,1:06:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MCGRATH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} If there's anyone profiteering\Naround here, it's you,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.23,1:06:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting in your fancy houses,\Ncozying up to the Brits.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.48,1:06:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the Liam I once knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.19,1:06:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You want the old me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.94,1:06:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Butcher of the Bogside,\Nis that what you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.70,1:06:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, hear this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.95,1:06:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You reel in those fuckin' cunts\Nand end it,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.20,1:06:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,or by God, I'll bury the lot of yas.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.83,1:06:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I'm going now.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.08,1:06:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be at my farm if you need me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.09,1:06:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And take care of that Committee issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.63,1:06:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want them jumping to the wrong\Nconclusion about that Semtex. Do we?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.97,1:07:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.22,1:07:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.14,1:07:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}EXHALES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.60,1:07:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you or any of the men know\Nwhere Mary's staying in London?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.44,1:07:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No one, but Murphy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.44,1:07:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. McGrath knows where she's hiding.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.03,1:07:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna know how.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.17,1:07:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.42,1:07:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SCOFFS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} What a day, Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.43,1:07:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KEYBOARD CLACKING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.47,1:07:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What a day. Come on now, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.35,1:07:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Charlie, up you get.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.86,1:07:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.55,1:08:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You killed my dog?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.06,1:08:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dog's fine. Just sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.35,1:08:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.52,1:08:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.36,1:08:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm wearing a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.40,1:08:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone comes in,\NI touch it one, then we die.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.78,1:08:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, give me the names.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.87,1:08:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They claim they're the IRA,\Nbut I don't know who they really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.75,1:08:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing everything I can\Nto find out who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.46,1:08:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lying! Who killed my daughter?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.79,1:08:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I truly don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.17,1:09:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.05,1:09:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The explosives the bombers use,\Nit's Semtex-H?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.35,1:09:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes. You know about Semtex?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.77,1:09:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Semtex-H.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.73,1:09:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,During the war,\NCzechs make for the Viet Cong.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.44,1:09:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for bombs and traps.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.82,1:09:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- In Vietnam?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.36,1:09:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Many American people died by Semtex-H.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.24,1:09:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, IRA use to kill my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.33,1:09:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ironic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.79,1:09:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read your history.\NWe both know about war.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.79,1:09:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We've both tried to put it behind us.\NYou and me, we're alike.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.13,1:09:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM GROANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.59,1:09:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We are nothing alike. You're nothing!\NYou kill women and children! Names!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.55,1:09:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- To Almighty God, I don't know!\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GUN COCKS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.72,1:09:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Wait. I've set a trap for them\Nwhen they use the next bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.85,1:09:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When they claim responsibility\Nfor the next bombing,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.43,1:09:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll use a code word,\Ntelling the police they're IRA.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.02,1:09:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've changed that code word.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.02,1:10:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when they use it, I'll know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.95,1:10:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You have one day.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.58,1:10:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they don't set off a bomb by then?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.96,1:10:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-four hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.54,1:10:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Jesus. Oh, Jesus. Sweet Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.51,1:10:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MIRA{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} We missed it the first time...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.55,1:10:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But ran a reconfiguration through RAPTOR,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.60,1:10:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and the image's anomalies\Nand architecture became more apparent.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.89,1:10:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there, look, the back of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.81,1:10:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Hmm.\N- Looks like a burn or a birthmark.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.60,1:10:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're running comparatives now.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.98,1:10:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's a bit more time,\Nbut we'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.53,1:10:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BELL TOLLING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.57,1:10:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.04,1:11:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}WOMAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.04,1:11:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.68,1:11:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BUS ENGINE STARTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.11,1:11:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PEOPLE SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.49,1:11:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CONTINUE SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.13,1:11:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY PANTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.61,1:12:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Good morning, Sean. Thanks for coming.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.53,1:12:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've been better.\NThere's been another bombing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.37,1:12:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, I just heard.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Aye, a London bus.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.87,1:12:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Has Bromley phoned?\N- No. Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.20,1:12:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,McGrath's on his way with some locals.\NThey'll give ya a hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.92,1:12:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't need them. I'll handle it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.79,1:12:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Good man.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.89,1:12:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE VIBRATING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.10,1:12:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hennessy.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.06,1:12:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They called, but didn't give a code word.\NWhat the hell's going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.03,1:12:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it wasn't them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.94,1:12:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Press Association took the call.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.11,1:12:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A man with an Irish accent said\Nthere'd be no more fuckin' cooperation
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.78,1:12:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Brits and no more code words.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.58,1:13:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew exactly which bus\Nand how much explosive was used.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.25,1:13:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's been ID'd as your Semtex again.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.46,1:13:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Either someone talked,\Nwarned them off, or you're playing me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.96,1:13:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Only two people knew what was happening...\NMyself and Morrison.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.34,1:13:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, one of you can't be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.80,1:13:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Send me a number where\NI can reach you day or night.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.64,1:13:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call the moment I have something.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.35,1:13:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It better be soon,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.85,1:13:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or you'll feel a backlash the likes\Nof which you've never felt before.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.15,1:13:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DAVIES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} A bus now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.65,1:13:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For God's sake,\N16 dead, twice that injured.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.40,1:13:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.24,1:13:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a plan to nail the bastards.\NDidn't work.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.33,1:13:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I've just come\Nfrom Downing Street.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.62,1:13:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The PM will consider the pardons,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.12,1:13:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but only if you give up\Nthe bombers immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.71,1:13:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And how in God's name do I do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.00,1:13:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DAVIES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Find a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.54,1:13:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Plans are afoot to put the paratroops\Nback on your streets in 48 hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.51,1:13:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Belfast will erupt.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.18,1:13:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll give the bombers\Nexactly what they want.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.72,1:14:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's out of my hands now.\NCall when you have something.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.93,1:14:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm heading for a conference\Nin Rome tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.56,1:14:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have my cell at all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.32,1:14:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.58,1:14:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How was London? Is Mary OK?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.67,1:14:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You said to keep an eye on her,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.34,1:14:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and make sure she and Keri were kept safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.47,1:14:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent some time in her hotel lobby\Nwatching the comings and goings, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.68,1:14:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She had no idea I was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.06,1:14:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And your nephew turns up.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.39,1:14:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He spent two hours in her room.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.19,1:14:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- He spent two hours in Mary's room?\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MURPHY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Aye.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.94,1:14:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And after he goes,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.45,1:14:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary comes down,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.78,1:15:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and calls Hugh McGrath on the lobby phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.97,1:15:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}RUSTLING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.18,1:15:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.60,1:15:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's done.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.31,1:15:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless they take it apart,\Nthere's no way to know it's been modified.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.03,1:15:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuckin' brilliant. What'll set it off?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.32,1:15:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The internal clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.61,1:15:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll input the time\Nonce we know the flight.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.45,1:15:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a security conference\Nin Rome tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.99,1:15:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All the top MPs and security people are\Nflying there on three lunchtime flights.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.66,1:15:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect. What about our mule?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.46,1:15:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sara just confirmed he's going.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.96,1:15:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We then ran the burn-mark\Nthrough the database.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.34,1:15:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a positive hit\Non a Patrick O'Reilly,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.38,1:15:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,age 29, from Belfast.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.67,1:16:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,O'Reilly had one prior for a domestic\Nabuse incident three years back.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.22,1:16:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Did two months in Hydebank.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.39,1:16:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We entered O'Reilly\Ninto the facial rec bank for matches.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.64,1:16:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a hit.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.02,1:16:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KEYBOARD CLACKING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.27,1:16:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's him in a Dublin pub\Nwith an IRA member four weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.98,1:16:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a known IRA meeting place\Nwe've had under surveillance for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.78,1:16:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}PRIME MINISTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\NAnd the other two with him?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.16,1:16:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I was about to get to them,\NMinister.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.08,1:16:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That and a woman we've just ID'd\Nat the bus explosion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.00,1:16:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KEYBOARD CLACKING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.54,1:16:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE VIBRATING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.75,1:16:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.17,1:16:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mole's Hugh McGrath.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.05,1:16:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear me, Hennessy?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.26,1:16:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure now?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.97,1:16:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.01,1:16:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We've ID'd the Knightsbridge bomber\Nas Patrick O'Reilly of Belfast.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.52,1:16:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Three weeks ago, Mr. O'Reilly was observed\Nmeeting Hugh McGrath in a Dublin pub.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.11,1:16:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's McGrath and O'Reilly now?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.36,1:16:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know O'Reilly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.03,1:17:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen McGrath.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.70,1:17:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me help you with McGrath.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.62,1:17:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,His phone's GPS puts him\N52 meters south of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.16,1:17:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm watching him coming up your drive.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.37,1:17:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's cut the shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.67,1:17:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a Chinook airborne\Nright now with a 12-man team.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.63,1:17:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll land on your farm in 30 minutes\Nto take McGrath into custody.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.30,1:17:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I needn't tell you how that'll go,\Nnor how your cozy relationship with him
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.38,1:17:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,will sink your career...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.18,1:17:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This time for good.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.43,1:17:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Or?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.52,1:17:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Question McGrath your way\Nand get what I need.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.23,1:17:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Names and locations of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.02,1:17:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't save him,\Nbut maybe you can save yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.56,1:17:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirty minutes, get what I need,\NI'll turn them around.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.82,1:17:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jim.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.99,1:17:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Send McGrath's men to the trailhead,\Nsee if Sean needs any help.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.34,1:18:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.80,1:18:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MCGRATH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} What the hell?\N- Give me your phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.55,1:18:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM BREATHES HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.34,1:18:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Get your ass in that chair there,\Nyou motherfucker.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.06,1:18:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- A London bus, for Christ sake!\N- Now hold on.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.18,1:18:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even fuckin' warnings!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.06,1:18:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixteen dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.69,1:18:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You stabbed me in the back\Nand sanctioned this bloodbath
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.57,1:18:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to get your war back on.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.03,1:18:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The plan had no balls.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.78,1:18:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This wasn't a Bombing Light campaign.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.95,1:18:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You said hurt 'em, and hurt 'em we did.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.99,1:18:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By killing women and children?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.45,1:18:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't restrain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.75,1:18:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You never could. Well, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.87,1:18:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Their names, aliases, and location.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.46,1:18:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I can't do that. {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.13,1:18:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's me being nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.96,1:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now write. And it better match\Nwhat I already know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.59,1:18:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,By God, I'll take you apart\Njoint by joint!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.97,1:18:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MCGRATH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You used me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.72,1:18:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanted the pardons\Nfor your own political gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.31,1:18:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a disgrace to the cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.44,1:19:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.11,1:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Four men and a woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.99,1:19:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Maggie Dunn?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.53,1:19:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye. You call her that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.37,1:19:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sara Mackay's her real name.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.46,1:19:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She works for you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.75,1:19:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloody right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.38,1:19:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Checks and balances.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.80,1:19:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SCREAMING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.34,1:19:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,An insurance policy,\Nin case you lose your nerve,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.60,1:19:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which you have.\NSo now, if they take the lads,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.35,1:19:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,she will lead them straight back to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.10,1:19:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so easy anymore now, is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.69,1:19:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,SO15 will be here\Nin 20 minutes to take you in.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.94,1:19:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We both know that can't happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.74,1:19:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You gave me up to the Brits?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.62,1:19:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You tout bastard!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.12,1:20:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You gave yourself up.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.50,1:20:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got surveillance of you\Nin an IRA pub with a Pat O'Reilly,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.30,1:20:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,who they ID'd as the Knightsbridge bomber.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.59,1:20:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And thanks to your GPS phone,\Nthey tracked you here.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.22,1:20:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SCOFFS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.72,1:20:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You broke every rule, Hughie.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.35,1:20:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'm left to clean up your mess\Nas I have for the past 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.61,1:20:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A final thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.03,1:20:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.87,1:20:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What about her?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.62,1:20:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SCREAMS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.04,1:20:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She hates you because of her brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.54,1:20:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so she reached out to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.38,1:20:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, I helped her...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.88,1:20:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And she helped me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.73,1:21:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GUNSHOT{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.98,1:21:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CELL PHONE RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.53,1:21:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Bromley.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.70,1:21:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I got your names.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.12,1:21:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.20,1:21:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BOTH PANTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.92,1:21:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit, I'm late. I've got to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.26,1:21:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you cum?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.42,1:21:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No. {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}CHUCKLES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}\NI'm not a three-second wonder like you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.93,1:21:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}IAN CHUCKLES{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.35,1:21:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}WATER RUNNING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.91,1:22:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DEVICE BEEPS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.87,1:22:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}WATER STOPS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.92,1:22:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GARGLING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.89,1:22:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, keep wearing that shirt,\NI'll be a two-second wonder.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.23,1:22:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna have to get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.52,1:22:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice, practice, practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.95,1:22:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm close.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.12,1:22:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} McGrath confessed.\NIt was his op all along.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.33,1:22:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got the bombers' names and location.\NI'll text you the info. You may need it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.13,1:22:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The one that killed Quan's daughter\Nis Pat O'Reilly.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.47,1:22:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a burn-mark on his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.59,1:23:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, Sean, you end this, now.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.10,1:23:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- You hear me?\N- Understood.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.09,1:23:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.51,1:23:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BOTH GRUNTING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.72,1:23:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN GRUNTS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.23,1:23:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BOTH GROAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.58,1:24:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}YELLS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.42,1:24:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN YELLS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.01,1:24:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GROANS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.60,1:24:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN BREATHING DEEPLY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.40,1:24:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You know why you're still alive?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.40,1:24:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} You want the names?\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.37,1:24:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SEAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} They're in the phone.\NThe last text, code 7741.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.21,1:24:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Five names and their location in London.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.33,1:24:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,O'Reilly set the bomb\Nthat killed your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.09,1:25:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a burn-mark on his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.51,1:25:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You fought in the army.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.64,1:25:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Iraq. Royal Irish Regiment.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.06,1:25:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Two tours, Special Forces.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.77,1:25:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Catholic,\Nbut you fought for British. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.23,1:25:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I fought for the regiment.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.36,1:25:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Out there, religion didn't matter.\NWe were all the same. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.82,1:25:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Family?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.58,1:25:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.45,1:25:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest have passed away.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.67,1:25:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}QUAN BREATHING HEAVILY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.41,1:26:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KNOCKING ON DOOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.37,1:26:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}SIGHS DEEPLY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.50,1:26:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come in.\N- {\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOOR OPENS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.00,1:26:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a seat, Sean.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.30,1:26:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye. You look like\Nyou've been through the wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.93,1:26:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye. Quan got the drop on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.56,1:26:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave him the names,\Nhe took my things and let me go.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.02,1:26:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When the bombers called in about the bus,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.19,1:26:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn't use a code word,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.57,1:26:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because someone tipped them off.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.57,1:26:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Only two people knew\Nthe reason for the code change.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.91,1:26:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You and me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.37,1:26:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Liam, I didn't tell anyone. I swear.\NI spoke to Bromley, and that was it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.12,1:26:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I told you I had Murphy stay
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.71,1:27:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and watch Mary in London?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.76,1:27:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My own flesh and blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.30,1:27:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Liam, I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.30,1:27:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna know\Nwhat happened in that room.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.43,1:27:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All I wanna know is, what was discussed
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.18,1:27:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when your sweet Aunt Mary was with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.85,1:27:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she say she was involved\Nwith McGrath and the bombers?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.32,1:27:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Never.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.40,1:27:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,She was upset about her brother\Nand kept on about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.44,1:27:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When you and I were talking\Nabout the code word, she asked about 'em,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.95,1:27:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but she never let on about McGrath.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.28,1:27:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so, she could hear us on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.53,1:27:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it was only after our call\Nshe mentioned the code word.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.95,1:27:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- She thought they wouldn't be of use.\N- So, she steered the conversation?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.16,1:27:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, I guess she did.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.75,1:27:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. A good manipulator, she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.92,1:27:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, she told the bombers?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.17,1:27:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She told McGrath, McGrath told them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.21,1:27:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thick as thieves, they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.47,1:27:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She tricked the information\Nout of ya, Sean.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.60,1:27:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She used you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.14,1:27:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Liam, I...\N- Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.27,1:28:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}LIAM SIGHS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.99,1:28:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Bury that pig in the sow-pen.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.32,1:28:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that,\NI have one final task for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.29,1:28:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that's done...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.33,1:28:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,go back to New York, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.99,1:28:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.62,1:28:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT CONVERSATION{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.58,1:29:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero, this is Alpha Two.\NEcho One toward target house.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.50,1:29:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ROSS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Zero. Echo One's\Ntoward the target house. Copy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.71,1:29:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ELECTRICIAN{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Echo One has entered\Nthe target house and unsighted to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.34,1:29:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero. Echo One is in target house\Nand unsighted to you. Copy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.39,1:29:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank Christ for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.10,1:29:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sierra call signs. Confirm when Echo One\Nis complete in target house.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.35,1:29:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sierra Two, roger that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.56,1:29:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sierra Three, roger that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.95,1:29:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,X-Ray One on balcony.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.20,1:29:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BROMLEY{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Echo One approaching front door.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.89,1:29:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.97,1:29:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's done.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.60,1:30:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}JOKER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I have visual. X-Ray One\Nand Echo One have left the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.19,1:30:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All other X-Rays remain.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.11,1:30:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}INDISTINCT CHATTER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.83,1:30:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero, this is Alpha Two.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.08,1:30:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,One unknown Echo and two children\Nentering the target house.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.79,1:30:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}ROSS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.94,1:30:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a slobbering oaf.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.56,1:30:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It had to be done.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.57,1:30:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to shag him.\NIt was fuckin' disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.44,1:30:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I know what you\Nwent through. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.57,1:30:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do ya, Denis? Do ya really?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.91,1:31:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe for the next bomb,\Nyou can set up a gay Magistrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.24,1:31:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How would that be?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.08,1:31:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking a shower.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.92,1:31:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}GUARD{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Next.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.23,1:31:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}JOKER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} X-Ray One entering living room.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.52,1:31:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All X-Rays now complete in living room.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.65,1:31:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All call signs\Nmove to your final rendezvous.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.80,1:31:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOG BARKS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.44,1:32:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,X-Rays and Echo complete in living room.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.70,1:32:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We've lost visual.\NEcho One has closed the blinds.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.04,1:32:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Fox One, you have control.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.00,1:32:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}JOKER{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Roger that. I have control.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.09,1:32:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Standby. Standby.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.47,1:32:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DOORBELL RINGING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.88,1:32:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, stop, stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.39,1:32:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}DENIS{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} Wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.52,1:32:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sierra call signs, report what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.98,1:32:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MI5 TECH{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b} I've two unknowns\Nat the front door. Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.23,1:32:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the bother,\Nbut there's a gas leak in the building,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.94,1:33:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gas man\Nneeds entry for an inspection.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.11,1:33:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our gas works fine. There's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.95,1:33:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs to inspect\Nall the flats, regardless.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.08,1:33:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't take a moment,\Nand it is an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.96,1:33:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}KNOCKING ON DOOR{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.25,1:33:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite important, Mr. Upton.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.96,1:33:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,By law, I'm allowed to use my own key.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.67,1:33:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Just a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.51,1:33:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}MOUTHING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.02,1:33:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Come down when you're done,\Nand I'll take you to the next flat.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.36,1:33:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I will be very fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.78,1:33:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.01,1:34:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I see the boiler, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.47,1:34:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind\Nputting your bag on the table?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.65,1:34:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Open it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.41,1:34:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\c&HFF759B&}({\c} {\fnMistral\c&H00FF80&}BAG OPENING{\fn\c} {\c&HFF759B&}){\c\b}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.08,1:34:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
